title: Nation mourns 15 victims of Bondi attack | 7NEWS
description: Australia observes a national day of mourning for 15 victims killed in the Bondi attack. Ceremonies take place across the country including at Bondi Pavilion, Martin Place, St Mary's Cathedral, and a central service at the Sydney Opera House featuring the Prime Minister and Governor-General. The Jewish community reclaims the Opera House two years after a controversial pro-Palestinian demonstration, with 15 pillars of light beaming across the nation and a call for five million acts of kindness. title: Gen Xers hold most property wealth in Australia
description: Gen Xers have overtaken baby boomers as holders of the most property wealth in Australia, a report by KPMG finds. The report also found that while some Gen Xers own a lot of property, others have none. #property #propertywealth #babyboomers #genX
